    {
      "id": "868c7b96-ee60-4d8e-a267-d8c83a64fb69",
      "name": "Sticky Note",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -1264,
        -768
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "width": 1152,
        "height": 928,
        "content": "# Automatic Airtable-to-Tempo Logger\n\n### Workflow Overview\nThis workflow automates your daily time-tracking routine by fetching logs from Airtable, submitting them to Tempo (Jira), and archiving the results.\n\n---\n\n### How it works\n* **Trigger:** Runs on a scheduled basis (default: 11 PM CET).\n* **Data Fetching:** Retrieves data from your \"Daily Worklog\" Airtable base.\n* **Processing:** Maps Airtable records to Jira Issue IDs and prepares Tempo payload.\n* **Tempo Submission:** Executes an HTTP request to submit your work time to Tempo.\n* **Maintenance:** Clears the \"Daily Worklog\" table and archives successfully processed logs into the \"Worklog History\" table.\n* **Notification:** Sends a direct Slack message confirming the successful upload.\n\n### Requirements\n* **Airtable Base:** \n    * Requires two tables: *Daily Worklog* and *Worklog History*. [Download Template Here](https://airtable.com/appPkZFrmA9yu0MxC/shrb4ohBr3k77hZj7)\n* **Credentials:** \n    * Airtable API Token\n    * Jira API Token\n    * Tempo API Token\n    * Slack Bot Token (`xoxb-...`)\n\n### Setup Instructions\n1. **Schedule Trigger:** Adjust trigger node to fit your preferred schedule.\n2. **API Credentials:** Set up your credentials in each corresponding n8n node.\n3. **Code Node Configuration:** Open the *Prepare Tempo Payload* node and update the `TEMPO_AUTHOR_ID` variable with your unique Tempo user ID.\n4. **Slack Integration:** Ensure your Slack bot has the `chat:write` scope and is properly authorized.\n\n### Customization\n* **Slack Notifications:** Modify the message text in the Slack node to your liking. Use [Slack's Block Kit Builder](https://app.slack.com/block-kit-builder) for advanced layouts."
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ab16606d-0642-43c8-ac86-5323c6ef245d",
      "name": "Sticky Note3",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        624,
        -512
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 7,
        "width": 632,
        "height": 416,
        "content": "### 2. Data Mapping, Payload Preparation & Tempo Upload\n\n* **Data Mapping**: Links Airtable records with Jira Issue IDs.\n* **Prepare Tempo Payload**: Calculates duration, sets author ID, formats timestamps and transforms input data into the required Tempo API schema.\n* **Tempo Submission**: Executes the HTTP POST request to upload the worklog into Tempo.\n"
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c4d0a61f-340b-4d03-8426-b7c432c01c17",
      "name": "Sticky Note4",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        1296,
        -512
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 7,
        "width": 416,
        "height": 416,
        "content": "### 3. Airtable History Log & Daily Table Cleanup\n\n* **Record History**: Archives processed entries into the Worklog History table to maintain a complete record of all submissions.\n* **Table Cleanup**: Deletes processed entries from the Daily Worklog table to keep it clean and ready for the next day."
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e0733566-6ace-41fc-aab2-0eebc6225b16",
      "name": "Sticky Note5",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        1744,
        -512
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 7,
        "width": 420,
        "height": 416,
        "content": "### 4. Data Aggregation & Completion Notification\n\n* **Aggregate Results**: Groups processed worklogs to generate a single output.\n* **Slack Notification**: Sends a Slack message confirming that the work logs were successfully uploaded to Tempo."
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
